editorialNotes.standard: Nothing beats a kid-friendly game that keeps the whole family captivatedand Toca has us snipping, straightening, and styling to our heart's content. Once we've perfected our customer's silly new dos, we make sure to add some accessories, snap a pic, and share the hair.

editorialNotes.short: Try a wild new look  risk-free!
editorialNotes.tagline: Go all out for crazy hair day!

editorialNotes.standard: What are those towers that touch the sky? Tinybops awesome sandbox teaches kids the fun wayby letting them build, watch, and play. As they add floors and test the effects of plumbing problems and earthquakes, they're actually learning basic design and engineering principles. Amazing details aboundfrom all the busy little inhabitants to the full-blown skyline you can make.
editorialNotes.short: Learn to build and manage a towering skyscraper.

name: Kids Vehicles: Construction HD for the iPad

editorialNotes.tagline: Interact with the power of nature
editorialNotes.standard: Part digital toy and part planetary handbook, The Earth gives kids insight into the workings of our world in a way thats delightfully intuitive and fun. From rockslides to earthquakes to erupting volcanoes, these artful interactive dioramas respond to tapping and swiping with results that are both whimsical and educational. An accompanying guide for parents and teachers delves into the technical science behind all these phenomena, but kids can explore, experiment, and absorb earthly knowledge at their own pace.
editorialNotes.short: Play with interactive models to understand our planet.

editorialNotes.standard: An utterly charming way to introduce young kids to music and animation, Loopimal is simple and powerful in a way that almost defies description. Kids arrange and rearrange tiles in sequences underneath a cute polar bear, octopus, and the like, triggering a series of musical tones mirrored by adorable dances from the animal gang. There are no goals and no consequencesjust a safe place to learn, play, and laugh.

editorialNotes.tagline: Build your own gears and engines

editorialNotes.standard: Ever pondered the atomic weight of Bismuth? Do you debate the density of Niobium over dinner? If so, this app is for you. Chemistry truly comes to life with this fully interactive version of the periodic table. Engage with the elements like never before and witness the wonders of science in beautiful detail.
editorialNotes.short: Chemistry comes to life with this interactive version of the periodic table.

editorialNotes.standard: Made with Tinybops usual charm and polish, Simple Machines distills difficult ideas into fun hands-on lessons. Spin giant screws, crack open icy boulders and use levers to bombard cartoon castlesall while learning about real-world physics.
editorialNotes.short: Interact with machines to understand physics.
Tinker with genetics to create cute monsters.

editorialNotes.standard: With Tinkerblocks, coding isnt just for big kids anymore. The simple interface lets little programmers combine graphical widgets to build fun, surprisingly sophisticated mini-apps that unleash their imaginations and teach coding fundamentals. We especially love how kids can access the camera, accelerometer and other features of their devices to instantly see the results of their work.
editorialNotes.short: Unleash imaginations and learn coding fundamentals.
